{"schema_version": "1.0", "timestamp": "2026-06-15T12:30:20.828608+00:00", "run_id": "20260615-222652-753877", "turn_id": "20260615-222721-932778", "event_id": "20260615-222652-753877-00008", "event": "assistant", "component": "integration", "phase": "output", "status": "completed", "source": "live", "message": "Assistant analysis result recorded", "duration_ms": null, "metrics": {}, "artifacts": [], "error": null, "payload": {"kind": "analysis_result", "content": {"input_type": "pdf", "input_ref": "[redacted-upload]", "metadata": {"title": "Retrieval-Augmented Generation for Knowledge-Intensive NLP Tasks Patrick Lewis\u2020\u2021, Ethan Perez\u22c6,", "authors": [], "paper_id": "tmpj9jln1gy_957527e7d7"}, "summary": "# Scope\nThe paper addresses knowledge-intensive NLP tasks where pre-trained language models struggle with accessing and manipulating explicit knowledge. It explores hybrid models combining parametric (e.g., seq2seq) and non-parametric (e.g., Wikipedia) memory to enhance performance on tasks requiring external knowledge.\n\n# Core Contribution\nIntroduces **Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)**, a general-purpose fine-tuning approach that integrates pre-trained seq2seq models with non-parametric memory (dense Wikipedia vector index) via a neural retriever. This enables models to dynamically access external knowledge during generation.\n\n# Method\n- **RAG-Sequence**: Uses the same retrieved document to generate the entire sequence.\n- **RAG-Token**: Leverages different documents per token for context.\n- Combines a pre-trained retriever (DPR) and seq2seq generator (BART), marginalizing over retrieved documents using top-K approximation.\n\n# Results\n- Sets state-of-the-art on three open-domain QA tasks, outperforming parametric seq2seq models and task-specific retrieve-extract architectures.\n- Generates more specific, diverse, and factual language for generation tasks compared to parametric baselines.\n\n# Limitations\nNo explicit limitations section was detected. The paper critiques evaluation scope via structural checks (e.g., missing clear metrics) but does not elaborate on limitations beyond these observations.", "key_findings": ["Core contribution: Introduces **Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)**, a general-purpose fine-tuning approach that integrates pre-trained seq2seq models with non-parametric memory (dense Wikipedia vector index) via a neural retriever. This enables models to dynamically access external knowledge during generation.", "Sets state-of-the-art on three open-domain QA tasks, outperforming parametric seq2seq models and task-specific retrieve-extract architectures.", "Generates more specific, diverse, and factual language for generation tasks compared to parametric baselines."], "research_gaps": ["Limitations: No explicit limitations section was detected. The paper critiques evaluation scope via structural checks (e.g., missing clear metrics) but does not elaborate on limitations beyond these observations."], "recommended_papers": [], "apa_citations": [], "evidence": [], "peer_review": null, "paper_analysis": {"keyphrases": [{"text": "single task retrieval", "score": 0.69, "section": "related_work", "source": "nadiyah_keybert_minilm"}, {"text": "non parametric memory", "score": 0.6375, "section": "discussion", "source": "nadiyah_keybert_minilm"}, {"text": "single wikipedia dump", "score": 0.6363, "section": "results", "source": "nadiyah_keybert_minilm"}, {"text": "models parametric memory", "score": 0.634, "section": "introduction", "source": "nadiyah_keybert_minilm"}, {"text": "non parametric memories", "score": 0.621, "section": "discussion", "source": "nadiyah_keybert_minilm"}, {"text": "nlp tasks", "score": 0.6171, "section": "related_work", "source": "nadiyah_keybert_minilm"}, {"text": "retrieval augmented generation", "score": 0.6159, "section": "abstract", "source": "nadiyah_keybert_minilm"}, {"text": "trained parametric memory", "score": 0.604, "section": "introduction", "source":