 as retrieval-augmented generation (RAG). We build RAG models where the parametric memory is a pre-trained seq2seq transformer, and the\nnon-parametric memory is a dense vector index of Wikipedia, accessed with a pre-trained neural\nretriever.", "candidate_sentence_count": 73, "source_traceable": true, "sentence_count": 5}}, "flags": {"retrieval_mode": "none", "retrieval_strategy": "hybrid_rrf", "model_mode": "base", "provider_sources": {"synthesizer": "live", "parser": "live"}, "ai_generated_sections": ["summary", "key_findings", "research_gaps", "peer_review"]}}}}
